@NODE DEST "Introduction"
@PREV INFO
@NEXT REQU

  TD_InsertCD is designed for opening and closing CD tray.
  TD_InsertCD works with drives controlled by devices that accept TD_EJECT
  (if you don't know, then run program and try it).
   ____                        ____
    /\                          ||
   /  \  - close tray          \  /  - open tray
    ||                          \/
@ENDNODE

@NODE REQU "Requirements"
@PREV DEST
@NEXT INST

  TD_InsertCD needs any Amiga with KS v37 or higher.
@ENDNODE

@NODE INST "Installation"
@PREV REQU
@NEXT PARMS

  Copy program with icon to desired place on disk.
@ENDNODE


@NODE PARMS "Arguments"
@PREV INST
@NEXT ATTN

  For CLI/Shell:

  DEVICE : device name e.g. cd.device, scsi.device. Default is cd.device.
  UNIT : unit number. Default is 0.
  X : horizontal window position.
  Y : vertical window position.
  PUBSCREEN or PS : public screen name where TD_InsertCD opens window.

  For Workbench:

  DEVICE,UNIT,X,Y,PUBSCREEN - same as for CLI/Shell. Write it in 
                              "Tool Types" window of icon.

  Example usage:
  TD_InsertCD scsi.device 2 X=500 Y=200 PS=DOPUS.1
@ENDNODE

@NODE ATTN "Important"
@PREV PARMS
@NEXT AUTH

  When program can't open cd.device, then "flashes" display.
@ENDNODE

